# 301s for removed blog posts → the closest surviving topical tag hub (not the
# generic /blog index, which Google can treat as a soft 404). Preserves whatever
# link equity these previously-indexed URLs earned.
/blog/seo-success-story/ /tags/seo/ 301
/blog/recovered-hacked-wordpress-site/ /tags/wordpress/ 301
/blog/responsive-blog-redesign/ /tags/web-development/ 301
/blog/custom-ecommerce-site/ /tags/web-development/ 301

# 301s for tag URLs that previously contained spaces (now slugified to hyphens).
# Cloudflare Pages serves this file from the build output. Only the two tags still
# used by a surviving post are kept; the others (custom-development, web-design,
# website-recovery, website-security) pointed at tag pages that no longer build
# after the post removals.
/tags/page%20speed%20optimization/* /tags/page-speed-optimization/:splat 301
/tags/web%20development/* /tags/web-development/:splat 301
